native_modules

This top-level module contains native modules that can be loaded into a Lua
instance via "require". These native modules are arch and platform specific
dynamic libraries that implement the Lua C-API to provide scripts with
functionality contained within externalized C functions.

See "HelloWorld" for an example of this functionality.

In the interest of keeping things contained, each module is kept in a
separate sub-directory, with a common Makefile that can be called to build
all modules. The resulting dynamic library will be created in the common
native_modules directory.

To add your own module, create a subdirectory with the POSIX and/or Windows
code and project file(s). Place module specific makefiles in this directory,
and augment the main Makefile to call it directly.

To build specific modules, you can run "make -f Makefile.MODULE_NAME", or
open the VS solution file on Windows.

On Windows, you will have to update the nmakefile to add the appropriate
recipes to the right targets. build.bat should not have to be modified.
This means that checkout should be able to find and build all native
modules from the native_modules directory.

Adding "native_modules" to a makelist should also do the right thing for
building with checkout. 
